%global pkg_name html-email-validate

%bcond_with tests

Name:           %{pkg_name}
Version:        0.2.0.0
Release:        0
Summary:        Validating an email address against HTML standard
Group:          Development/Libraries/Haskell

License:        BSD-3-Clause
Url:            https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}
Source0:        https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}-%{version}/%{name}-%{version}.tar.gz

BuildRequires:  ghc-Cabal-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-rpm-macros
BuildRequires:  ghc-attoparsec-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-text-devel
%if %{with tests}
BuildRequires:  ghc-QuickCheck-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-hspec-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-regex-pcre-builtin-devel
%endif

%description
The library allows to validate and parse an email address as it's defined in
<https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/forms.html#valid-e-mail-address HTML
standard>. Note that HTML specification of a valid email address is a 'willful
violation' of RFC 5322. If you want to validate an address against RFC 5322 you
should use <https://hackage.haskell.org/package/email-validate email-validate>.


